contentrichtext.text: '''Ginn''' or '''GINN''' may refer to: *[[Jinn|Ginn]], supernatural beings in Arab folklore and Islamic teachings. *[[List of Stargate Universe characters#Ginn|Ginn]], a recurring character appearing in the television series ''Stargate Universe''. *[[Mobile_weapons#Mobile_suits_in_Cosmic_Era|GINN]], a fictional, mechanical exoskeleton weapon suit, worn in the ''[[Gundam SEED|Mobile Suit Gundam SEED]]'' [[anime]] television series. *[[Ginn (software)|Ginn]], a [[daemon]] program for [[Linux]] that gives [[application software|applications]] the ability to support a subset of [[multi-touch]] gestures on [[touch-sensitive]] displays. *''[[Ginn & Co Solicitors]]'', a Cambridge-based law firm, which was established in 1873 by Samuel Reuben Ginn *[[Ginn and Company]], UK publisher, part of the [[Penguin Group]] **Ginn Publishing Canada *[[Bob Ginn]], the owner of Ginn Clubs and Resorts real estate company and owner of the NASCAR Nextel Cup team Ginn Racing. *[[Greg Ginn]], American guitarist, formerly of hardcore punk band [[Black Flag (band)|Black Flag]]. *[[Samuel Ginn]], a pioneer in wireless communications and namesake of the Samuel Ginn College of Engineering at Auburn University. *[[Ted Ginn, Jr.]], an American football wide receiver who currently plays for the [[San Francisco 49ers]] of the National Football League. {{disambiguation}}
